{{Commons category|Flora of Australia by state or territory}}
This category contains flora that are native to, or naturalised in, [[Australia]]. Taxa that are introduced but not naturalised are excluded. Taxa of the lowest rank are always included. Higher taxa are included only if endemic.

The categorisation scheme follows the [[World Geographical Scheme for Recording Plant Distributions]], in which Australia is as politically defined except for the following exceptions:
* the [[Australian Antarctic Territory]] is not included in Australia; it is treated as part of the [[Antarctic]] continent;
* [[Heard and McDonald Islands]], politically a territory of Australia, is treated with the other subantarctic islands;
* [[Macquarie Island]], politically an island of [[Tasmania]], is treated with the other subantarctic islands;
* [[Christmas Island]] and [[Cocos (Keeling) Islands]], both territories of Australia, are treated as part of [[Malesia]].
The subcategories are as politically defined except:
* The [[Ashmore and Cartier Islands|Ashmore and Cartier Islands Territory]] is treated as subordinate to [[Western Australia]];
* The [[Australian Capital Territory]] is treated as subordinate to New South Wales;
* The [[Coral Sea Islands|Coral Sea Islands Territory]] is treated as subordinate to [[Queensland]];
* [[Jervis Bay Territory]] is treated as part of [[New South Wales]];
* [[Lord Howe Island]], politically part of New South Wales, is treated as subordinate to [[Norfolk Island]].

